http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Thu 6 Oct 2011
Source: Bloomberg Businessweek [edited]
http://www.businessweek.com/news/2011-10-06/italy-reports-seven-new-cases-of-anthrax-in-widening-outbreak.html


Italy reported 7 new cases of anthrax in livestock since last week
[week of 26 Sep 2011] as the deadly animal disease spreads in the
country's south, bringing affected farms to 26 since the 1st
confirmation in September 2011.

The illness killed cattle, sheep, and horses or donkeys on 7 farms
across 4 towns southeast of Naples, Italy's Ministry of Health said in
an alert today [6 Oct 2011] published online by the Paris-based World
Organization of Animal Health, or OIE. One of the towns had no
previous occurrence.

Animals died on 4 farms in Pietrapertosa as well as on farms in
Corleto Perticara, and Padula, adding to previously reported cases,
according to the alert. Italy also found anthrax in Laurenzana, the
1st case there, it showed.

The outbreak continues, and measures to fight the disease include
animal-movement controls and disinfection of infected farms, the
animal-health group said. Livestock is not being vaccinated, the OIE
said.

[Byline: Rudy Ruitenberg]

