[2]
Date: 4-5 Oct 2011
Source: EU Commission, Standing Committee on the Food Chain and Animal
Health (SCFCAH), Italian Ministry of Health, Department for Veterinary
Public Health, Nutrition and Food Safety report [edited]
http://ec.europa.eu/food/committees/regulatory/scfcah/animal_health/presentations_en.htm#23102007
http://ec.europa.eu/food/committees/regulatory/scfcah/animal_health/presentations/0405102011_anthrax_italy_en.pdf


Italy: anthrax outbreaks in 2011
--------------------------------
23 outbreaks have been reported in Campania (7 outbreaks in Salerno)
and Basilicatta (3 outbreaks in Materra and 13 in Potenza).

Control measures, as provided by current national rules (D.P.R. n
54/320), have been adopted: demarcation of infection zone (3 km [2 mi]
radius); restrictions of animal movements; destruction of dead animals
and vaccination of all susceptible animals. Outbreaks have been
officially notified to OIE (with the exception of those confirmed last
week).

The NRL [national livestock service] is looking, together with the
local competent authorities, on the origin of the outbreaks and
extending the control measures in place on those areas (such as
extension of the vaccination period). In the coming days further
information will be made available.

